        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer73796272" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14748861909404758859">This is, hands down, the scariest book I have ever read. Ever. I read it for the adrenaline genres week in my Reader&apos;s Advisory class. Since I only had a couple of days to read this and another book (716 pages in 2 days!), I stayed up till about 2 am reading this. <b>BAD IDEA!!</b> I started out reading it in the lounge, but moved into my room at some point. And that was when the trouble started. At some point I needed a bathroom break. But I was too scared to open my door and run the 3 feet to the bat</span>
  <span id="freeText14748861909404758859" style="display:none">This is, hands down, the scariest book I have ever read. Ever. I read it for the adrenaline genres week in my Reader's Advisory class. Since I only had a couple of days to read this and another book (716 pages in 2 days!), I stayed up till about 2 am reading this. <b>BAD IDEA!!</b> I started out reading it in the lounge, but moved into my room at some point. And that was when the trouble started. At some point I needed a bathroom break. But I was too scared to open my door and run the 3 feet to the bathroom. I was afraid the bad man from the story would be out there. I'd like to take this moment to point out that I was 27 when I read this.</span>
