    <a title="Reginas..Haunted..Library" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/102002644-reginas-haunted-library"><img alt="Reginas..Haunted..Library" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1567103018p2/102002644.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3100441006?book_show_action=true">Dec 26, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Reginas..Haunted..Library" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Reginas..Haunted..Library" href="/user/show/102002644-reginas-haunted-library">Reginas..Haunted..Library</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/102002644-reginas-haunted-library?shelf=horror">horror</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/102002644-reginas-haunted-library?shelf=weird">weird</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3100441006" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer413525721340810354">A Dantesque journey into the depths of hell, Barker&apos;s ambitious, first full-length novel is beautifully written and includes some of the grossest descriptions I have ever read. Whereas many of Barker&apos;s stories fly off the rails when his intense imagination starts firing on all cylinders, this narrative remains fully under the master storyteller&apos;s control. The build is slow and steady until the gory climax that left me stunned, shaken, and extremely grossed out. I loved it!</span>
  <span id="freeText413525721340810354" style="display:none">A Dantesque journey into the depths of hell, Barker's ambitious, first full-length novel is beautifully written and includes some of the grossest descriptions I have ever read. Whereas many of Barker's stories fly off the rails when his intense imagination starts firing on all cylinders, this narrative remains fully under the master storyteller's control. The build is slow and steady until the gory climax that left me stunned, shaken, and extremely grossed out. I loved it!</span>
