<span id="freeTextContainer17435245690675907028">Clive Barker was just a few descriptions of maggot-infested flesh away from writing a horror masterpiece.Oh, there are many scenes resplendent with rotting, flayed flesh (almost always with a vague sexual undertone), but one or two more would have definitely done wonders for &quot;the horror&quot;.<br/><br/>The worst thing about The Damnation Game is that it&apos;s not uninteresting or bad enough to warrant quitting in the beginning. Readers with misguided principles (like me) of not abandoning a book after a certain nu</span>
  <span id="freeText17435245690675907028" style="display:none">Clive Barker was just a few descriptions of maggot-infested flesh away from writing a horror masterpiece.Oh, there are many scenes resplendent with rotting, flayed flesh (almost always with a vague sexual undertone), but one or two more would have definitely done wonders for "the horror".<br /><br />The worst thing about The Damnation Game is that it's not uninteresting or bad enough to warrant quitting in the beginning. Readers with misguided principles (like me) of not abandoning a book after a certain number of pages turned will be kept in literary limbo.</span>
